ytical. Through a singular feminist revision of a traditional poetic form, they tell the story - sometimes raunchy, sometimes crushingly sad - of a strong protagonist and the predicament she's in.  aMode of access: Internet via World Wide Web.  aIn English.0 aDescription based on online resource; title from PDF title page (publisher's Web site, viewed 29. Mai 2023) 0aElectronic books. 0aLove poetry, CanadianxHistory and criticism. 7aPOETRY / Canadian.2bisacsh40uhttps://doi.org/10.1515/978077359702040uhttps://www.degruyter.com/isbn/9780773597020423Coveruhttps://www.degruyter.com/document/cover/isbn/9780773597020/original  aGBV-deGruyter-alles